text: The Gurglbach is a river of Tyrol, Austria. The Gurglbach originates on the rock face near Nassereith. It flows from west to east to Tarrenz, the only village that it passes completely through. There, it changes its route and flows south to Imst where it merges with the river Inn away from the town. It has a length of . The river is one of the cleanest waters of Tyrol. It is a calm, slow running brook. ==References== Category:Rivers of Tyrol (state) Category:Rivers of Austria
